[
{ type: install
  message: <<EOM
 You must create the configuration files yourself. A minimal example
 configuration has been installed to %%ETCDIR%%/dovecot.conf.
 Edit it to suit your needs.

 For full configuration documentation, see:
 https://doc.dovecot.org/

 Next, enable dovecot in /etc/rc.conf:

 	dovecot_enable="YES"


 To avoid a risk of mailbox corruption, do not set the
 security.bsd.see_other_uids or .see_other_gids sysctls to 0
 if Dovecot is storing mail for multiple concurrent users (PR 218392).

 Similarly, setting sysctls security.bsd.hardlink_check_uid or
 security.bsd.hardlink_check_gid to 1 might result in non-working
 mailboxes, depending on what mailbox locking mechanism is used
 (PR 242223).


 IMPORTANT: Dovecot 2.4.x is NOT backward compatible with Dovecot 2.3.x.
 If you are upgrading from Dovecot 2.3, you MUST read the migration guide
 before starting Dovecot 2.4:

   https://doc.dovecot.org/2.4.0/installation/upgrade/2.3-to-2.4.html

 The configuration format has changed significantly. Review and update
 your configuration files before starting the new version.
EOM
}
{
  type: remove
  message: <<EOM
If you are removing dovecot permanently, you should 'rm -rf /var/db/dovecot' to
clear out any remaining data.
EOM
}
]
